An amazing time-lapse video has squeezed the Mars Curiosity rover's nine-month mission into just one minute of viewing.

The incredible clip is the work of Karl Sanford, of Grand Rapids, Michigan, who claims that it's his first time making such a video.

Downloading the raw images from the Curiosity website, Sanford arranged the photos from the rover's front left hazcam and into an MPEG format. He uploaded the video to YouTube on May 22.Â 

